><br>So the answer is anywhere a warrior can MT for exp groups.<br><br><br><br>(I have no Primal, just use Tstaff to MT.  No NToV gear, just good old Skyshrine &quot;whitelotus.&quot;  But 60+ AA.)<br><br>And I tank for almost all my exp groups.  I am the only one who can consistantly hold aggro over our rogues.  The warriors just can't do it in most cases without the rogues having to seriously back off their damage output.  What good is that IMO when I can take the damage or not take it so to speak just as well and allow your DD's to destroy the mob faster than with a warrior MTing because the DD's have to reserve their big damage till the end.<br><br><br>People will make the argument (old and tired one) that CH isn't as effective on a monk as a warrior because of less HPs on the monk.  <br><br>Here is the otherside of it.  The fight won't last as long with a monk MTing because he/she can hold aggro with more ease and it frees your DDs up to unleash their worst.  So the fight doesn't last as long.<br><br><br><br> <p>Rhizzen Khillahpriest <Darkblood> <br>54 Necromancer of Innoruuk<br>Sol Ro<br><br>Sensai Ssoulz Jah <Darkblood><br>60 Grandmaster of Cazic Thule<br>Sol Ro<center><img border="0" src="http://www.thedragonseye.net/eq/Sensei%20Ssoulz%20signature.jpg" width="508" height="239"> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urhizzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhizzen</A> at: 7/18/02 9:03:49 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udenonia2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>denonia2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/21/02 11:02:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1007.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where to M